# finsec-ops Cursor Rules

Read `README.md` and `TODO.md` before making changes. Confirm the active
development phase and work only within that phase unless explicitly instructed
otherwise.

Project scope: cybersecurity financial operations for CISOs and cybersecurity
leadership. Support budgets, planning, forecasting, vendors, resellers,
contracts, products, modules, renewals, procurement lifecycle, financial
reporting, and executive reporting. Do not turn the product into GRC, ERP,
accounting, ticketing, vulnerability management, asset inventory, or project
management software.

Code standards: strict TypeScript, small reusable components, business logic
outside React components, modular services, interchangeable providers,
composition over duplication, minimal dependencies, and readable production
code.

Architecture standards: separate UI, services, providers, database, and
utilities. Document meaningful decisions in `architecture/decisions`. Update
README and relevant docs when architecture, folder structure, data model,
technology, workflow, deployment, or testing changes.

Phase 0 is foundation only. Do not add authentication, CRUD, Prisma models,
migrations, financial calculations, AI functionality, notifications, or real
business workflows until a later phase explicitly authorizes them.
